when someone calls you their muse what does that mean exactly in greek mythology there were muses immortal daughters of one of the immortal titans each muse had a science or art that they were protectors of and therefore were inspirations for you can read more about them here http library thinkquest org inhabitants demons site htm so the term today means to be the living embodiment of creative inspiration for someone usually an artist if you ever see the movie xanadu olivia newton john plays terpsichore the muse of song i believe on roller skates EastEnders Time Out of Mind Jon Secada Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Friends Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Cliff Richard W.I.T.C.H. One Tree Hill (TV series) Paul Is Dead Neighbours Days of our Lives Scenes from a Memory Salad Fingers The Subtle Knife Jean Grey Blood on the Tracks Journey (band) Poker jargon Sin City Futurama (TV series - season 5) The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Miss Saigon Ocean's Twelve Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) The Ashlee Simpson Show Planning and execution of the September 11, 2001 attacks The Curse of Fenric The Time Machine Frankie Laine Pitaten The Beatles The Death Gate Cycle Philip J. Fry Hall & Oates Social rule Socrates Little Britain Daredevil Glen Jacobs Guiding Light G-Man (Half-Life) Another Side of Bob Dylan Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) Nightmare (Soul Calibur) Jiddu Krishnamurti The Parting of the Ways Hey Jude The Pilgrim's Progress Tag Plame affair A Course In Miracles Rod Stewart Oasis (band) The Shining (film) Donovan History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Twin Peaks Samurai Deeper Kyo Tenchi Muyo! Hip hop collaborations New York Giants Yoko Ono John the Baptist Prince Edmund (Blackadder) Empire Burlesque AFI 100 Years series Wheel of Fortune Alfred Hitchcock The Beach Boys Characters in the Smurfs The Smoking Room Fitz Hugh Ludlow 2004 Republican National Convention Elvis Presley Mojave people Phaedo Charl